Let's take random varibale of weights of people 
X = {43,23,24,41,25,62,87,91,45,90,87}

We can plot over X- Axis the points that exists such that we draw 
distribution line of all the points. This is called 
the histogram
Between 20-30 -> 3 points 
Between 30-40 -> 0 points 
Between 40-50 -> 3 points 
Betweeb 50-60 -> 0 points 
Betwen  60-70  -> 1 point 
Between 70-80 -> 0 points 
Between 80-90 -> 3 points 
Histogram is plotted with bins, 0-10 1 bin, 10-20 another bin like that 
X axis bins and Y axis frequency: 1 2 3 count how many points 
are there in each bin 
We have 2 types of histograms, continous and discrete, with each 
we get different types of hostogram 

We can derive probability density function from histogram 
by making curve which is touching all the bins 
The smoothening one is called the kernel density estimator 

histogram -> Kernel Density Estimator -> Probability Density Function 
